CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1772745125
OL,3,CWoman died days after telling staff
OL,4,Cshe would 'throw herself into sea'
OL,6,FTwo days later, she disappeared.
OL,8,FFollowing Mrs Potter's death, an
OL,9,Fexternal, independent review was
OL,10,Fcarried out and concluded that several
OL,11,Fareas of Jersey's Mental Health
OL,12,FDepartment need to be improved.
OL,14,FThey include:
OL,16,FDuring the inquest at Morier House in
OL,17,FSt Helier, the Police Coroner Officer,
OL,18,FKate Falle, read several witness and
OL,19,Fcharacter statements - including one
OL,20,Ffrom a family friend.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G4/6
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,384,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1772745125
OL,3,CWoman died days after telling staff
OL,4,Cshe would 'throw herself into sea'
OL,6,FThis friend believes Mrs Potter's
OL,7,Fdeath was "preventable" and "cannot be
OL,8,Fbrushed under the carpet".
OL,10,FIn response, Jersey's Health
OL,11,FDepartment has welcomed the
OL,12,Frecommendations laid out in the
OL,13,Findependent review.
OL,15,FIn a statement, the island's Director
OL,16,Fof Mental Health, Andy Weir, adds: "I
OL,17,Fwould like to offer my deepest
OL,18,Fsympathies to Mrs Potter's family.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G5/6
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,384,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1772745125
OL,3,CWoman died days after telling staff
OL,4,Cshe would 'throw herself into sea'
OL,6,F"Health and Care Jersey are committed
OL,7,Fto reviewing any incident of suspected
OL,8,Fsuicide and identifying areas where we
OL,9,Fcould improve our services or take
OL,10,Factions that may have helped to
OL,11,Fprevent this."
OL,13,FThe Coroner concluded that while the
OL,14,Fcause of Mrs Potter's death could not
OL,15,Fbe determined, she did intend to take
OL,16,Fher own life due to her ongoing
OL,17,Fmedical issues.
OL,19,FHe stated that the role of the inquest
OL,20,Fis to determine how someone died and
OL,21,Fnot who may have been responsible.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G6/6
